Description: Fragment of handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora; fine buff clay; circular stamp with rose symbol.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Mytion. The handle was analysed by Hans Mommsen, Bonn, with NAA and is a chemical loner; the results of the analysis are not yet published
Name, Mytion. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0171.04 and BM 1874,0805.63.
